snippet: Jennara Cobb had faced up to a year in prison for warning fellow police officers about a wiretap investigation into a widespread practice of making traffic and parking tickets disappear.
abstract: Former New York City Police Lieutenant Jennara Cobb is sentenced to 200 hours of community service for warning fellow officers about investigation into ticket-fixing; had faced up to year in prison for divulging eavesdropping warrant, official misconduct and obstruction of governmental administration.
lead_paragraph: Jennara Cobb had faced up to a year in prison for warning fellow police officers about a wiretap investigation into a widespread practice of making traffic and parking tickets disappear.
